If human nature was one set pattern, Communists wouldn't exist, end of story.<br>
Societal nature is a whole nother story now ain't it? You are instilled with the values of your society. Hence, were Communism to ever be implemented and generations grew up on it, you would notice a shift in general &quot;human nature.&quot;<br>
Read again Wallace, I never said Communism couldn't or hasn't worked large scale, I said it has NEVER BEEN ATTEMPTED on a large scale. That isn't opinion, that is fact.<br>
